sections.comments: For students unable to register for PSYC 218 (for example students with year 1 standing on the SSC or unclassifed students)  please do not contact the instructor.  You can complete the Request to be Added form using the following link, which will record the details of your request, and instruct you how to proceed.  Please note that students are expected to register in any section with available seats that fits into their timetable before submitting a request.We will contact students only if we are able to accommodate their add requesthttps://ubc.ca1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_a9jNmzDtG4Yp9hX

description: Use of inferential statistics in psychology and conceptual interpretation of data; experimental design (laboratory, field research methods); presentation of data analyses in reports. PSYC 218 excludes credit for a number of other statistics courses in various departments. Please consult the Science Exclusion List (www.students.ubc.ca/calendar/index.cfm?tree=12,215,410,414) before registering. Credit will be granted for only one of PSYC 218 or PSYC 278.
